Mith Marr &lt;Ilsik Haucil&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqumdaila.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qumdaila</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/24/02 2:26:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Paludal Caverns</span><hr size=1> Actually Paludal caverns is one of the best levelling spots i have ever found for my twinks/chars between level 10 and 25 - the lower level mobs are over near shadeweavers thicket side, kill them and the plerg fiends until you are high enough to do the bandits.<br>
 <p><center><img src="http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Qumdaila/fullsize/Sig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushizzanidiot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShizzaNidiot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/25/02 10:52:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizard for you?</span><hr size=1> Tetsuo,<br>
<br>
Not to be a downer or anything, but if you are only 9th level, and already asking questions like these, and being concerned about how fast you level...the Wizard class may not be for you.<br>
<br>
We are, arguably, one of the slowest exping class out there.  That little comment about money not being a factor means nothing for leveling a Wizard.  Wizard twink stuff doesn't increase the speed in which we level like it does for melee's, and even other casters in some cases.<br>
<br>
If you are playing a Wizard because you love the class, and enjoy playing it, then by all means find out what the &quot;quickest way to level&quot; is...<br>
<br>
But, I submit to you, if you are looking for the quickest way to get Manaburn, then you need to go ahead and stop now because you are going to frustrate yourself.  <br>
<br>
Good luck to you,<br>
<br>
Shizz<br>
 <p>Shizza Nidiot
Sorceress Companion to the Chetari Rats of Dragon Necropolis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyndbender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myndbender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/26/02 6:57:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard for you?</span><hr size=1> i'd have to agree with Shizz, the life of a wizard is not the easiest one in everquest. Levels seem to come as slowly as groups do especially for a casual player. At around level 9 i was killing stuff in sro (dervs and orce iirc) and at 16 i moved on to NK to kill beetles (learned with my bard that these things run as fast as you do, so you don't really need sow, just a head start). beetles took me to 21 or 22 and then i moved up to maru seru till 32, then off to kill drakkel wolves for a while in GD, then i started grouping in Tenebrous mountains and then into Scarlet desert at 45 or so.<br>
<br>
The wizard class imho is the best in the game (for my play style) but i get bored of nuking every once in a while and pick up my bard for a few nights.<br>
<br>
Bards are a fun and challenging class to play and can do well solo and seem to be always wanted in a group.<br>
<br>
just my couple of copper.<br>
<br>
Australis ~ Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udizzera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dizzera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/26/02 10:17:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard for you?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Shiz as well.  If you are just planning to have someone on a burn squad.... be prepared for a long and very tedious life where the end may not justify the means.  My wiz is recently 51 and over 2 years old &lt;no i don't play as much as some&gt;  and have led what I consider to be a good wizardly life.  IE some grouping, some solo, some raiding, some questing, etc.  <br>
<br>
my 2cp <p><img src="http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/14/14731/pages/105006/dragonsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyiar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yiar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/26/02 11:19:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard for you?</span><hr size=1> Everything said here is completely true.  Moreover, a wizard really doesnt come into his own until the mid to late 40s, arguably even his 50s.  Fact of the matter is, there is no easy way to level a wizzy.  All the &quot;easy&quot; ways, such as quadding, kiting, etc take a lot of time, a lot of patience, and a LOT of downtime.  Unfortunately, you really cant do those things until you get to at least 16 or so, and then they're still really hard.  I didnt master kiting until I was nearly 25, and quadding until I was nearly 40.  Now I go and do them no problem, but I still prefer the group atmosphere.<br>
<br>
If you want to level up a character fast and do incredible damage, might i suggest the way of the rogue or the warrior?  Easily twinkable, fast to level, and everyone wants one in their group.  On most blue servers, everyone looks down on the low level wizard (read everyone that is *NOT* 60), and its near impossible to get groups.  Get a good group of friends, find some spots that you like, and stick with them for a while.  The only way your going to be respected is to learn your class, and let people know that you know how to play.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of good wizards out there that better our reputation as a whole, and then there are those that keep us down in the slumps.  It takes a good wizard to level, it takes a patient wizard to level, and theres usually a good chanter behid them too =)<br>
<br>
If you really want to be a wizzy, stick it out, but dont expect things to come easy for you.  The only gear that even remotely helps wizzies level is FT gear, or items with free nukes on them, but your not going to see those for a LONG time.<br>
<br>
Yiar<br>
59.3 Evoker<br>
Resolution -Firiona Vie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usenwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>senwiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 12:45:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard for you?</span><hr size=1> I must agree with the sentiments expressed here. I too was like you. It took me awhile to get beyond that level 10 bareer (Sp?) Being a DE I ran around Nektulos, EC, WC, and NRO at level 9. That is about the fastest way I know. Groups are very hard. Sometimes you find people that don't understand what our class is truly about, and that is ashame really. Everyone I know, from my younger levels is now 34 plus. However, a friend of mine, a Wizard, says that we really don't come into our own until 29, when we get snare, and really can't solo stuff big time until 34.<br>
