 <p><img src=http://www.cableone.net/aozzy/sig1.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvymdraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vymdraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/2/02 2:39:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I love my wizard</span><hr size=1> Ah, the life of a wizard, it can be hard but it is incredibly rewarding. I have been plaing for not even a month now and am halfway though level 27. I have spent the majority of my time hunting in HP and HK and am now looking for a new hunting spot. The only problem I have ever had with being a wiz is not being able to get into groups but rather actually getting ANY loot. In 11 levels I have only made 23p, 8g, 4s, and 7c, no items, and the occasional rune (if I'm lucky). The rewarding part is criting on a nuke for over 200 dmg and blam, its dead. I am on the Bertox server and for some reason the tanks here are incredibly greedy, lucky for me I found a great way to make money at level 20 or I would be totally broke. My advise is this: if your going to play a wiz try to find a regular group of people to play with so that when you are medding up you won't be getting the short end of the stick on looting. And in a few more levels soloing will be the only way to go.<br>
<br>
Patience, skill, and a little luck are the tricks to being an awesome wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utaarne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taarne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/29/02 8:53:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I love my wizard</span><hr size=1> I've played three wizards in the 3-4 years I've been playing Everquest. Cendywen, at level 29, is the highest of them (others have been 20 and 24), and they've all been slow to level.<br>
<br>
Soloing can make you frustrated and depressed. Avoid poor looking pickup groups, but do group once in a while, for it's so much fun be able to do massive dmg, and save the group by rooting and nuking an unwanted add in 15 seconds, while the rest of the group goes &quot;Wow!&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Twinking a wizard does not make him much faster to level, unless you can in some absurd way get ahold of lots and lots of Flowing thought gear.. What I recommend you to get is, DD and mana recuding focus items.. It lowers the downtime, and thus reduces the frustration. HP items are also good, as they will reduce the amount of deaths by _a lot_. Believe me, before lvl 29, you will die a lot if you are unsowed and/or have crappy hp. Mana won't be that big of a matter before you start quading, but it's always nice to have a good sized manapool.<br>
<br>
Leveling a wizard is soooo much easier than it used to be, provided you have a little bit of cash, or enchanter friends. You probably guessed why, it's all thanks to KEI. With it, you can gain level sooo quick, as long as you can avoid deaths.<br>
<br>
-Rotbone Binkbonk, 56th lvl Oger shaman<br>
-Cendywen, 29th level high elf wizard<br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umuklestikk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukle Stikk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/02 8:25:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I love my wizard</span><hr size=1> Let me first say that I have played a Monk to 60 a cleric to 49 and a Wizard to 51 and the one that I leveled the fastest is the wizard by far.<br>
<br>
I repectfully disagree with all of you.<br>
<br>
XP is only slow in the lower levels.  Getting to 19 or so was kinda slow but not a whole lot slower then the other classes.  Getting a group as a wizzy is very hard at higher levels but at lower levels you can usually get in.  Once you hit 18 or so go to Paludal.  I was getting a full blue solo there a kill and with KEI it is very very fast xp.  You can xp there all the way till about 25.  mobs start to LB at 24.<br>
<br>
24 to 38 or so was fairly slow for me.  Spent a lot of time wandering around.  Get in a decent guild with people your  level and try to go to a few dungeons.  Sol A is pretty nice.<br>
<br>
I went from 38 to 51 in under 2 weeks so who ever thinks wizards level slow hasn't played any other classes.  I have never seen such insane xp I was getting while quading in IC and TD.  It took me a hell of a lot longer to get my monk and my cleric through these levels.  Even going from 51 to 60 as an Iksar monk was a royal pain in the butt.  Having to find a good group that would go to a dungeon and play long enough to make it worth while.  I hated those stupid encs and clerics that left 30 minutes after we finally got to chardok or HS.<br>
<br>
With KEI you can get about 3 to 4% per quad.  I am only lvl 51 now but I am certain I wasn't getting 3 to 4% per quad as fast as my monk was getting group xp.  The best thing of all is that you don't need groups.  You are always ready to solo.  Just send a tell to the many level 60 ENCs on your server that have KEI, My friends list is has quite a few, then offer 50pp and a port if they would like one for KEI.  Most ENCs have no problem casting it if you run to them.  There are many places to solo on luclin, kunark and velious some are a little tougher then others but practice makes perfect.  There is a lot of good info in these boards of places to hunt.  IMHO wizards are the fastest leveling characters.<br>
<br>
Ephraim the Channeler of FV <p>Mukle Stikk<BR>
