<img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/deadpool/muklesig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaxilsolshok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daxil Solshok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/02 9:59:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=513.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://daxil.htmlplanet.com/images/eq000093.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I love my wizard</span><hr size=1> I posted this on the Caster's Realm:<br>
<br>
First, on grouping. <br>
<br>
My main is a wizzy and I've never had problems finding groups. Some say it is the hardest class to find groups with, but like all the others it depends on your personality. <br>
<br>
1.) You must have patience when looking for a group on any given day. Are you willing to spend the time to think of a good place to camp, and then ooc or shout for other peeps to join you? This can take up to a half hour, and no, no one will ever seek you out. Until 29+ your a wimp and everyone knows it. But you do have one advantage at 20+ - self port. You must be proactive and use it to your advantage. Shout &quot;lfg&quot; in the zone, send tells to your friends, form groups, whatever, but you must be proactive. <br>
<br>
2.) You must have patience when leveling up. If your a true noob, it will take you about 20 levels before you start playing the wiz correctly - if you ever do. It's about this time that your melee skills are out damaged about 30-1 by the tanks and you are forced to sit and nuke. 20-30, however, your nukes are still not effective enough to make you very valuable. It's about this time that most non wiz-oriented personalities, i.e. impatient people, stop playing their wiz. From my experience its about 30-35 when people will accept you as a valuable member of a group. No, they still won't seek you out, but if you ooc that your looking for group you'll be invited just as often as most other classes. That's when your crits really start getting up there, you have group evac, and, theoretically, you know how to use the wizard properly. Its my opinion that most people give you the benefit of the doubt at 30+ because you SHOULD know what your doing by then. If you didn't you'd be playing a druid, the easiest class to play in the game... <br>
<br>
3.) You must start to use the wizard properly before you can expect re-invites and smiles. There is nothing worse then over nuking as it is high profile. Suddenly all the tanks have nothing to swing at and you have a wiz standing there stupid with a mob or two pounding on them. This usually results in multiple tells from most of your group trying to explain to you how to play your class. You see, a wiz can kill most mobs in the same time it takes most tanks to bring it down to 75 percent health. Its very easy to get that itchy trigger finger and try to prove you are the best character in the game. You should not. However, depending on how much damage output your tanks deliver, and/or the healing power of your primary healer, you'll want to vary the timing of your nukes. In that way the wiz class can become interesting, and it requires a lot of groundwork and practise to get your timing down. In some cases you'll want to ride the edge and exert the maximum ammount of damage possible without drawing aggro, and occasionally you will draw the ire of a mob - just don't do it twice, or a tight ass leader may just boot ya. <br>
<br>
On the positive side, a good wizard will speed up the pull rate of a group. Before level 29 or so, most people won't openly acknowledge you, but you can silently smile to yourself when you see them type &quot;wow, we're getting experience fast.&quot; Later on, it's an ego boost when you make that 500+ crit and the average melee puts out an 80 crit. Oh, and manaburn (Wiz AA ability) is simply the most powerful weapon in the game. 15k+ in unresistable damage tends to bring down most bosses. That's when you feel your true power  And the evac spell at 18, that is the best way in the game to get people to remember who you are and re-invite you later. You'll have everyone praising you - silently and out loud. Don't evac too soon though - again, another timing issue. And finally on raids, wizards/druids are integral to getting everyone to the raid spot, and wizards alone are integral for translocating everyone away from the raid spot to the place of their choosing. That's the time when everyone lines up and pays homage to you asking for ports all at once LoL.<br>
<br>
4.) And perhaps most important for anyone who likes to group - You must have a good personality. There is nothing more annoying than being grouped with someone inconsiderate in terms of loot and demands/undeserved arguments with other group members. <br>
<br>
After that long winded explanation I move on to soloing pre level 29 wizards are the worst soloing class in the game. Post level 29 they are equal to or better than any class as soloing. See: Bonds of Force area effect snare spell. That said, most wizards tend not to be solo oriented...they'd never make it to 29...they'd be a druid  <br>
<br>
Finally, nukes fizzling. yes it happens, but a warrior sometimes misses when he/she swings. In fact, sometimes the warrior wiffs 7 or 8 times. the point: yes you do get resisted, but not too often unless your facing a much higher level mob. At that point besides ports, and until the Draught line of spells, your nukes are useless. <br>
<br>
The wizard class really is a rewarding class to play. Granted I have not made the end game yet, but from all I've heard it only becomes moe enjoyable as you get bigger. That certainly has been the case from my perspective. If I could sum up a wizard in a sentence: They are the class that can immediately change the outcome of a group situation faster than any other class out there...for better or for worse. Oh, and they are a class completely based on proper timing and feel for a situation as aforementioned. Now, feel free to be a druid if ya want..just don't take it personally when I rib ya :P <br>
<br>
Daxil Solshok <br>
